  "structure": {
    "frequencyPerWeek": "2-3",
    "dayAlternation": "A on odd sessions, B on even",
    "sliders": { "moves": [3, 15], "cool": [1, 2] },
    "selection": "Each move carries goalScores (trainingGoalId -> 0..3). A move's base score = Σ over training goals of goal.weight × goalScore; moves scoring 0 are excluded. A recency boost favours moves not done recently. Moves are then picked greedily up to `moves`, with per-section diminishing returns (each already-picked move discounts its section) so Floor never crowds out Weights / Machines; the picks are grouped by section into Floor / Weights / Machines.",
    "notes": [
      "Warm-up and cool-down are static and always cover the care goals (splits, plantar, cubital, posture, sciatic, recovery); only change them when the user explicitly asks",
      "Training goals (flip, aerial, core, gym) have 0–10 weight sliders in Settings; weight 0 turns a goal off. Care goals are always on and have no sliders.",
      "Health constraints: cubital tunnel (no hard elbow lockout pressing), plantar fasciitis (keep slow calf loading, conservative impact), sciatic nerve (gentle flossing lives in user's splits routine), posture (never drop the pulling work), user stims by jumping (extra daily impact through feet)"
    ]
